fdryDaiMIB.name: fdryDaiMIB

revisions.description: Changed the ORGANIZATION, CONTACT-INFO and DESCRIPTION fields.

fdryDaiMIB.description: Management Information for configuration of Dynamic ARP Inspection feature. Dynamic ARP Inspection is a security mechanism which validates all ARP packets in a subnet and discard those packets with invalid IP to MAC address bindings. ArpType.name: ArpType
ArpType.description: Represents type of ARP entry to be used.

ArpState.name: ArpState
ArpState.description: Represents state of ARP entry to be used.

fdryDaiVlanConfigTable.name: fdryDaiVlanConfigTable
fdryDaiVlanConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to control Dynamic ARP Inspection per VLAN. When a VLAN is created in a device supporting this table, a corresponding entry of this table will be added.

fdryDaiVlanConfigEntry.name: fdryDaiVlanConfigEntry
fdryDaiVlanConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration to enable or disable Dynamic ARP Inspection at the existing VLAN.

fdryDaiVlanVLanId.name: fdryDaiVlanVLanId
fdryDaiVlanVLanId.description: This object indicates the VLAN number on which Dynamic ARP Inspection feature is configured.

fdryDaiVlanDynArpInspEnable.name: fdryDaiVlanDynArpInspEnable
fdryDaiVlanDynArpInspEnable.description: This object indicates whether Dynamic ARP Inspection is enabled in this VLAN. If this object is set to 'true', Dynamic ARP Inspection is enabled. If this object is set to 'false', Dynamic ARP Inspection is disabled.

fdryDaiIfConfigTable.name: fdryDaiIfConfigTable
fdryDaiIfConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to configure the trust state for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose at each physical interface.

fdryDaiIfConfigEntry.name: fdryDaiIfConfigEntry
fdryDaiIfConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration to enable or disable trust state for Dynamic ARP Inspection at each physical interface capable of this feature.

fdryDaiIfTrustValue.name: fdryDaiIfTrustValue
fdryDaiIfTrustValue.description: This object indicates whether the interface is trusted for Dynamic ARP Inspection. If this object is set to 'true', the interface is trusted. ARP packets coming to this interface will be forwarded without checking. If this object is set to 'false', the interface is not trusted. ARP packets received on this interface will be subjected to ARP inspection.

fdryDaiArpInspectTable.name: fdryDaiArpInspectTable
fdryDaiArpInspectTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to control Dynamic ARP Inspection entries. When an IP-MAC mapping entry is created in a device supporting this table, a corresponding entry of this table will be added.

fdryDaiArpInspectEntry.name: fdryDaiArpInspectEntry
fdryDaiArpInspectEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration to map a device IP address with its MAC address.

fdryDaiArpInspectRowStatus.name: fdryDaiArpInspectRowStatus
fdryDaiArpInspectRowStatus.description: This variable is used to create, or delete a row in this table. When a row in this table is in active(1) state, no objects in that row can be modified except this object.

fdryDaiArpInspectType.name: fdryDaiArpInspectType
fdryDaiArpInspectType.description: The type of the ARP entry

fdryDaiArpInspectState.name: fdryDaiArpInspectState
fdryDaiArpInspectState.description: The state of the ARP entry

fdryDaiArpInspectAge.name: fdryDaiArpInspectAge
fdryDaiArpInspectAge.description: The timer of the ARP entry

fdryDaiArpInspectPort.name: fdryDaiArpInspectPort
fdryDaiArpInspectPort.description: The port of the ARP entry
